  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Provision of life-saving interventions in Ebola pandemic response in North Kivu province, Democratic Republic of the Congo</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The main objective of this project is to provide life-saving health, water, sanitation, and protection assistance to vulnerable communities in regions affected by, and those at risk of, Ebola. This UNICEF project raises awareness about infection prevention and control measures; improves water, hygiene and sanitation in health facilities; provides psychosocial support to Ebola patients and their families and to healthcare workers; continues to provide access to basic essential services for gender-based violence and the prevention of sexual exploitation and abuse. The water, sanitation and hygiene component of the project provides life-saving assistance to 8,400 people, including 1,764 women, 1,680 men, 5,000 children, and 250 people with disabilities. The protection component of the project provides life-saving assistance to 7,100 people, including 1,350 women, 1,200 men, 4,500 children, and 220 people with disabilities. The health component of the project provides life-saving assistance to 3,900 people, including 590 women, 1,370 men, 1,900 children.</narrative>
  </description>
